Remote system : GITHUB 
Local system : OUR PC 

1. To add a github repo to our system we use command : git clone <url>      (url of the repo from github)

2. To list all items : ls
3. to list hdden items : ls -a   or   ls -h

4. To change directory : cd <name of the directory>     

5. To check status : git status

6. To add changes done in a file : git add <file name>
7. To add all the changes done : git add .

8. To commit changes : git commit -m"<the message for commit>"

9. To push your code : git push origin <branch name>     or    git push -u origin <branch name>

10. To exit a directory : cd ..
11. To make a new directory : mrdir <name of directory>

12. To make a directory a git directory : git init

13. To add a new local file on github .... First make a repo on github without readme file, then in the terminal of the new file : git remote add origin <url>   

14. To check what our current remote repo is : git remote -v

15. To check ehat our current branch is : git branch
16. To change the name of the current branch : git branch -M <name of the branch>

17. To create a new branch : git checkout -b <name of new branch>
18. To navigate from one branch to other : git checkout <branch name>
19. To delete a branch : git branch -d <branch name>

20. 